BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:33218
DTSTAMP:20260314T020700Z
SUMMARY:The Little Dancer: A Reimagining of Le Petit Prince (R)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.lincolnwoodlibrary.org/event/little-dancer-reimag
 ining-le-petit-prince-33218
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251230T154408Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260223T174106Z
DESCRIPTION:Ede2 celebrates its 15th Anniversary with an original dance pro
 duction “The Little Dancer: A Reimagining of Le Petit Prince” written
  by Antoine de Saint-Exupéry. The out-of-this-world production will foll
 ow the story of a pilot marooned in the desert when they meet the mysterio
 us stranger who traveled to Earth from a far away asteroid in search of th
 e meaning of connection and friendship. This family-friendly show features
  an eccentric cast of characters who populate various planets\, such as sp
 ace royalty\, a talking rose and a friendly fox\, who all teach The Littl
 e Dancer unique lessons on becoming a good person and how to care for othe
 rs.All ages are welcome to attend. Children must be accompanied by a careg
 iver.
CATEGORIES:History & Culture,Special Events
DTSTART:20260315T200000Z
DTEND:20260315T210000Z
LOCATION:4000 W. Pratt Ave.\, Lincolnwood\, IL\, 60712\, US
GEO:42.0047721;-87.7292067
END:VEVENT
