SUMMARY:*RESCHEDULED* Words That Change Lives: A Conversation with Chicago 
 Books to Women in Prison (R)
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.lincolnwoodlibrary.org/event/rescheduled-words-ch
 ange-lives-conversation-chicago-books-women-prison-r-35353
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260310T220945Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260310T234835Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for an inspiring evening that explores the power of boo
 ks to heal\, connect\, and transform lives. In partnership with Chicago Bo
 oks to Women in Prison\, we’ll learn how access to reading supports educ
 ation\, reflection\, escape\, and much more for women and trans people who
  are incarcerated. Volunteers from the organization will share their exper
 iences sending books to readers behind bars\, and we’ll hear from someon
 e who will share how the program supported them during their time in priso
 n and beyond.
CATEGORIES:Adult Learning
