BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:33657
DTSTAMP:20260314T020700Z
SUMMARY:Navigating News Media with Michael Spikes [Z]
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.lincolnwoodlibrary.org/event/navigating-news-medi
 a-michael-spikes-z-33657
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260115T144940Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260116T004352Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a virtual session of the Civic Empowerment Series 2
 026\, presented in partnership with Schaumburg Public Library and other ar
 ea libraries. Dr. Michael A. Spikes of Northwestern University’s Medill 
 School of Journalism will explain how today’s media landscape—shaped b
 y social platforms\, mixed information sources\, and AI-generated content
 —can make it difficult to know what to trust. Learn practical strategies
  for evaluating credibility and building a reliable set of news sources yo
 u can use with confidence.The Civic Empowerment Series 2026 is brought to 
 you in partnership with Schaumburg Public Library\, Skokie Public Library\
 , Vernon Area Public Library\, Blue Island Public Library\, Highland Park 
 Public Library\, Aurora Public Library District\, La Grange Public Library
 \, Fox River Valley Public Library\, Algonquin Area Public Library Distric
 t\, Roselle Public Library and Oak Park Public Library. Please note: On t
 he Schaumburg Township District Library registration page\, please select 
 online. Schaumburg Township District Library will email a Zoom link three 
 hours prior to the start of the program.This program will take place on Zo
 om.Register Here!
CATEGORIES:Community Engagement,Adult Learning
DTSTART:20260401T000000Z
DTEND:20260401T010000Z
LOCATION:US
END:VEVENT
