SUMMARY:Monday Matinees
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.lincolnwoodlibrary.org/event/monday-matinees-3500
 6
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20260225T154014Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260302T213930Z
DESCRIPTION:Enjoy great films at your library every Monday! Doors open at 1
 2:45pm.  Eternity (2025)Mon\, Apr 6 • 1-3pm • PG-13\, 112 mins • 
 [D]In an afterlife where souls have one week to decide where to spend eter
 nity\, Joan is faced with the impossible choice between the man she spent 
 her life with and her first love\, who died young and has waited decades f
 or her to arrive. Sinners (2025)Mon\, Apr 13 • 1-3:30pm • R\, 128 mi
 ns • [D]Trying to leave their troubled lives behind\, twin brothers retu
 rn to their hometown to start again\, only to discover that an even greate
 r evil is waiting to welcome them back. Song Sung Blue (2025)Mon\, Apr 2
 0 • 1-3:30pm • PG-13\, 133 mins • [D]Two down-on-their-luck performe
 rs form a Neil Diamond tribute band\, proving it's never too late to find 
 love and follow your dreams. Hamnet (2025)Mon\, Apr 27 • 1-3:30pm • 
 PG-13\, 125 mins • [D]William Shakespeare and his wife\, Agnes\, celebra
 te the birth of their son\, Hamnet. However\, when tragedy strikes and Ham
 net dies at a young age\, it inspires Shakespeare to write his timeless ma
 sterpiece Hamlet.
CATEGORIES:Movies\, Music & Entertainment
